cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a novel method for estimating the intrinsic dimensionality of a dataset, which is a common problem in machine learning and data analysis. The method uses both normalized nearest neighbor distances and angles between neighboring points, which are features commonly used in computer vision and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper also mentions experiments on both synthetic and real datasets, which suggests that it could also be relevant to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
